<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="304" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,215,1269]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,712,737]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaffer" authorityYear="1763" box="[476,600,712,737]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[476,600,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">Libelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a characteristic faunal element of the Palaearctic region. Despite the status of some taxa needs to be evaluated, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaffer" authorityYear="1763" box="[629,753,748,773]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[629,753,748,773]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">Libelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes at least 19 species of which about 12 are present in Europe, mainly in the western Mediterranean area (H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Aspock, H. &amp; Holzel, H. &amp; Aspock, U." box="[766,982,783,808]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="1 - 606" refId="ref15410" refString="Aspock, H., Holzel, H. &amp; Aspock, U. (2001) Kommentierter Katalog der Neuropterida (Insecta: Raphidioptera, Megaloptera, Neuroptera) der Westpalaarktis. Denisia, 2, 1 - 606." type="journal article" year="2001">
Aspöck 
<emphasis box="[858,915,783,808]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
). The larval morphology and ecology of this genus are poorly known: the first accurate study on this subject was realized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brauer, F." box="[1095,1253,819,844]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="463 - 472" refId="ref15963" refString="Brauer, F. (1854) Beitrage zur Kenntniss des inneren Baues und der Verwandlung der Neuropteren. Verhandlungen des Zoologisch-Botanischen Vereins in Wien, 4, 463 - 472." type="journal article" year="1854">Brauer (1854)</bibRefCitation>
while the genus characters of the larvae were defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hagen, H. A." box="[606,765,854,879]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="33 - 62" refId="ref16310" refString="Hagen, H. A. (1873) Die Larven von Ascalaphus. Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung, 34, 33 - 62." type="journal article" year="1873">Hagen (1873)</bibRefCitation>
. Notably only two recent comparative works on this subject exist (
<bibRefCitation author="Rousset, A." box="[223,384,889,914]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="164 - 178" refId="ref17391" refString="Rousset, A. (1973) Morphologie externe et caracteres distinctifs des larves de trois especes d'Ascalaphes [Nevropteres, Planipennes]. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 78, 164 - 178." type="journal article" year="1973">Rousset 1973</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pieper, H. &amp; Willmann, R." box="[400,700,889,914]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref17155" refString="Pieper, H. &amp; Willmann, R. (1980) Die Larven griechischer Ascalaphiden-Arten (Ins., Planipennia). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, 337, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1980">Pieper &amp; Willmann 1980</bibRefCitation>
). The larvae of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Selys-Longchamps, 1840)" baseAuthorityName="Selys-Longchamps" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[894,1306,889,914]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cunii">
<emphasis box="[894,984,890,913]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">L. cunii</emphasis>
(Selys-Longchamps, 1840)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brulle, 1832)" baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacteus">
<emphasis box="[1322,1435,889,914]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">L. lacteus</emphasis>
(Brullé, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schneider, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Schneider" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[363,745,925,950]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhomboideus">
<emphasis box="[363,538,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">L. rhomboideus</emphasis>
(Schneider, 1845)
</taxonomicName>
are actually known (
<bibRefCitation author="van der Weele, H. W." box="[979,1206,925,950]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="31 - 32" refId="ref17602" refString="van der Weele, H. W. (1909) Ascalaphiden monographisch bearbeitet. In: Collections Zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps, Catalogue Systematique et Descriptif, 1908 8, 1 - 326. [date of distr.: 5. I. 1909 cf. Cowley, J. (1937) The dates of distribution of the fascicles of the &quot; Catalogue des collections de Selys Longchamps. Journal of the Society for the Bibliography of Natural History, 1, 31 - 32.]" type="journal article" year="1909">van der Weele 1909</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Navas, L." box="[1217,1353,925,950]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="373 - 398" refId="ref16811" refString="Navas, L. (1915) Neuropteros nuevos o poco conocidos (IV serie). Memorias de la Real Academia de Ciencias y Artes de Barcelona, 11 (3), 373 - 398." type="journal article" year="1915">Navás 1915</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pieper, H. &amp; Willmann, R." pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref17155" refString="Pieper, H. &amp; Willmann, R. (1980) Die Larven griechischer Ascalaphiden-Arten (Ins., Planipennia). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, 337, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1980">Pieper &amp; Willmann 1980</bibRefCitation>
) but their descriptions are excessively concise or referring to not diagnostic instars, for this reason adequate comparisons are not normally possible with the exception of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brulle" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[1027,1136,996,1021]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lacteus">
<emphasis box="[1027,1136,996,1021]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">L. lacteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tentatively inserted in the key. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation author="Navas, L." box="[359,511,1031,1056]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" pagination="373 - 398" refId="ref16811" refString="Navas, L. (1915) Neuropteros nuevos o poco conocidos (IV serie). Memorias de la Real Academia de Ciencias y Artes de Barcelona, 11 (3), 373 - 398." type="journal article" year="1915">Navás (1915)</bibRefCitation>
described a larva as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rambur, 1842)" baseAuthorityName="Rambur" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[750,1089,1031,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanicus">
<emphasis box="[750,900,1031,1056]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">L. hispanicus</emphasis>
(Rambur, 1842)
</taxonomicName>
, but this identification appears questionable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,215,1269]" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1102,1127]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The larvae of the different species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaffer" authorityYear="1763" box="[742,867,1102,1127]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="304" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[742,867,1102,1127]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="304">Libelloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show a noticeable overlapping in the macroscopic characters normally used for identification purposes, such as: chaetotaxy, morphometry and the general pigmentation pattern. The relative difficulty to find the larvae in the field and their camouflaging behaviour make these light differences even more unsuitable. In particular, their camouflage is so effective that the different species are not recognizable if not artificially cleaned making visible the pigmentation pattern.
</paragraph>
